    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1056"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1056">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss
                        target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 324</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        French Prime Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MFP1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mendès-France</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1056fn1">The text of this letter was
                        transmitted to Washington in telegram 179 from Paris, July 14.
                        (751G.00/7–1454; <hi rend="italic">Pentagon Papers</hi> [Gravel Edition],
                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 554–557) Copies of the letters
                        exchanged by <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendès-France</persName> were provided to Foreign
                        Secretary <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> by the French Premier.
                            <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> acknowledged receipt by
                        letter of July 14. (Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss target="#t_CF1"
                            >CF</gloss> 324) <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>’s letter
                        was also included in telegram 179 from Paris of July 14.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-14">July 14,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I have received your letter of
                    July 14<note n="2" xml:id="d1056fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1055">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> with reference to participation by the United States in the
                    final stages of the Indochina phase of the Geneva Conference.</p>
                <p>In the light of what you say and after consultation with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>, I am glad to be able to inform you
                    that the President is asking the Under Secretary of State, <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGWB1">General Walter Bedell Smith</persName>, to prepare to
                    return at his earliest convenience to Geneva to share in the work of the
                    Conference on the basis of the understanding which we have arrived at.</p>
                <p>I greatly appreciate the opportunity which we have had to confer together, and I
                    believe that it has added a new chapter to the honorable and precious tradition
                    of Franco-American cooperation.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John Foster Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
